snippet.title: Amber Heard’s defense tries to dismiss Johnny Depp’s libel lawsuit in the United States
snippet.description:
Amber Heard’s defense tries to dismiss Johnny Depp’s libel lawsuit in the United States – Explica.co.
For those who thought that the legal dispute between Johnny Depp (Minamata – 35%, Waiting for the Barbarians – 51%) and Amber Heard (Aquaman – 73%, Justice League – 41%) had already ended, the reality is that They still have a long way to go, as their trial in Virginia, United States, will begin in July and the consequences could still be harsh for either side.
However, after The Sun defeated Depp in the lawsuit for the defamation lawsuit that the actor filed against the British media for calling him a ‘wife beater’, now the defense of the actress is trying to dismiss the lawsuit that the protagonist of Pirates of the Caribbean filed against her in Virginia alleging the verdict of the jury in the United Kingdom.
For Depp’s defense, this is just one last desperate move or ‘Hail Mary’ for the trial to no longer proceed (via CinemaBlend).
To stay up to date with latest top stories, make sure to subscribe to this YouTube channel by clicking the button above this video!
